description.narrative: (Kenya): The Human Resources for Health project will strengthens health workforce management systems at county and national level to achieve improved family health outcomes. The project will directly supports faculty pedagogy and andragogy skills, post training measurement, county led in-service training coordination, and institutional-based in-service trainings towards better performance and improved skills for family health interventions. The project will support improve human resource management and leadership skills to enhance efficiency among family health workforce at county and facility levels. There will be deliberate interventions towards optimization of data use for effective decision-making to improve distribution, recruitment, retention, and productivity of workforce that support family health activities in a bid to ensure equity in workload across the various service delivery points. The project will work to support the community health workforce, a critical component to increase access to family health services and secondarily towards achieving Universal Health Coverage. By utilizing a health systems strengthening approach, the project ensures sustainability upon project completion, which is vital to achieving the Kenya Integrated Country Strategy Goal 3, and U.S Department of State and USAID Joint Strategic Plan 2018-2022 objective which seeks to promote healthy, educated, and productive populations to drive inclusive and sustainable development. Improving global public health supports the Administration's priority of asserting U.S. leadership and influence..
